			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">To clarify, there used to be bugs in the triangle channel but they had nothing to do with the channel not turning on - they were causing the duty cycle counter to glitch in strange ways. The reason you weren't getting output is because you weren't doing enough to actually turn on the channel, and the following writes (slightly reduced from above) are enough to do that:<br /><br />$04 -&gt; $4015 - enable the channel<br />$7F -&gt; $4008 - set the linear counter reload value to something nonzero<br />$04 -&gt; $400A - set the frequency<br />$00 -&gt; $400B - set the frequency and length counter<br />$80 -&gt; $4017 - clock the frame counter, triggering a linear counter reload and unsilencing the channel</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
