					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Quietust wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">To clarify, there used to be bugs in the triangle channel but they had nothing to do with the channel not turning on - they were causing the duty cycle counter to glitch in strange ways. The reason you weren't getting output is because you weren't doing enough to actually turn on the channel, and the following writes (slightly reduced from above) are enough to do that:<br /><br />$04 -&gt; $4015 - enable the channel<br />$7F -&gt; $4008 - set the linear counter reload value to something nonzero<br />$04 -&gt; $400A - set the frequency<br />$00 -&gt; $400B - set the frequency and length counter<br />$80 -&gt; $4017 - clock the frame counter, triggering a linear counter reload and unsilencing the channel</div><br /><br />Thanks, that worked.<br /><br />Here's a test program (assembled opcodes within []) and a URL showing that there's no limit on the triangle's frequency. (If there are simpler ways to poke values, that would be nice to know.)<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">$04 -&gt; $4015 &#91;A9 04 8D 15 40&#93; (enable triangle channel)<br />$7F -&gt; $4008 &#91;A9 7F 8D 08 40&#93; (set the linear counter reload value to something non-zero)<br />$04 -&gt; $400A &#91;A9 00 8D 0A 40&#93; (set frequency low (to highest possible frequency))<br />$00 -&gt; $400B &#91;A9 00 8D 0B 40&#93; (set frequency high and length counter)<br />$80 -&gt; $4017 &#91;A9 80 8D 17 40&#93; (clock frame counter, reloading the linear counter and unsilencing the channel)<br />CLC BCC #$FE &#91;18 90 FE&#93;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;(loop endlessly)<br /></div><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/chipimages/visual2a03/?graphics=false&amp;logmore=Execute,tri_en,tri_on,tri_p,tri_t,tri_out&amp;a=0&amp;d=a9048d1540a97f8d0840a9008d0a40a9008d0b40a9808d17401890fe">http://www.qmtpro.com/~nes/chipimages/v ... 17401890fe</a><!-- m --><br /><br />During cycle 41 tri_out starts changing at the rate of the CPU clock.</div>

