					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">ulfalizer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is the sweep unit addition carry out also tied into the mix?</div><br />Yes - at t12636, inverted carry output drives node 10636 low (and at t12546, the sweep direction flag does the same, ensuring that it can only trigger silence if it's in &quot;add&quot; mode), and node 10636 is one of the 4 signals that can force square0 to output zero instead of the duty cycle (the other 3 are the length counter, the duty cycle, and &quot;freq &lt; 8&quot;).<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">ulfalizer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Do you know when that addition is done?</div><br />The addition itself is done <strong>continuously</strong> - the only thing that happens at a particular time is the result of the addition being stored back into the frequency register.</div>

					
