				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That's exactly what's going on.<br /><br />One specific thing to notice is <em>why</em> node 10094 is powered by default. If you jump to node 12942 and then look immediately to the right, you will see a purple rectangle that's part of 10094 which is connected to VCC on the left and <em>itself</em> on the right (the poly has a small &quot;hook&quot; on the right which connects directly to the bit of diffusion using a &quot;buried contact&quot;, which is a via between poly and diffusion). That particular bit is effectively a <em>pull-up resistor</em> (it's actually a transistor whose threshold voltage is below GND, leaving it permanently enabled); if you look around the chip, you will see <strong>hundreds</strong> of them scattered all over the place, most commonly in places that have registers.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">ulfalizer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Hence, 10094 will only be high at the top (after it has passed sq0_p3) if <em>all</em> of sq0_3 to sq0_10 are low. Therefore, 10094 must be the NOR of sq0_3 to sq0_10.<br /><br />If you keep going, you can then see that 10094 being high would cause 10512 to be low (cause it to drain into ground), etc.</div><br />Node 10094 also goes downward and then to the right, and at t12613 it drives 10653 low in order to make the channel output 0 instead of the current volume (10653 gets buffered into 13041 during odd clocks, 13041 gets inverted into 10626, and 10626 drives all of sq0_out to GND whenever it's high).<br /><br />Node 10512 is what allows the sweep unit to actually update the frequency, and it's a 7-input NOR gate, the other 6 inputs being 10509 (shift count zero), 10514 (sweep disabled), 10524 (length counter zero), 10636 (sweep frequency sum overflow), 12922 (sweep timer overflow), and 10563 (frame sequencer not at half-frame).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
